  "narrative": "DRIVER\nCHF leads D1 CSM at 100 but is the most critical divergence signal in this session: H4 CSM has CHF fading to 32 while GBP surges to 100, a 68-point H4 gap that overrides the D1 risk-off narrative and flags a live short-term regime shift. GBPCHF is the cleanest expression, amplified by GBPUSD H4 strong correlation at 0.93 with GBPJPY, meaning GBPJPY confirms the GBP leg independently. The counter-narrative is real: news bias is USD bullish with hawkish Fed repricing, and USDJPY D1 signals Strong Buy, so any GBP rally that stalls at resistance hands initiative back to JPY crosses on the D1 frame.\n\nMOMENTUM\nGaining: None\nFading: AUDJPY H4 momentum at 43 and dropping sharply while D1 holds 52, NZDJPY H4 fading to 47 with USDCAD D1 surging to 72\n\nWATCH\nBoJ commentary on bond volatility hits USDJPY directly, D1 Strong Buy signal triggers acceleration toward prior highs\nFed speaker repricing on hawkish tone pressures EURUSD through the 0.61 inverse USDJPY correlation amplifying the USD leg\nOil slide continuation below 102 on Iran talks hits USDCAD, where D1 momentum at 72 accelerates the CAD-weak trend",
